4:
Oh, not again... Guess I went a little
overboard.
12:
Hey, Marly! What're you doing
picking boulderberries? Don't tell me
you're THAT hard on coin.
15:
They were my daughters' favorite. I
can have myself a pity party now
and then, can't I?
17:
Yeah, yeah... Say what you want, but
you're better off for it, aren'tcha?
19:
Hold up. If you're feelin' lonely, how
'bout the two of us—
21:
Ugh... What's that smell? You been
rolling around in a porker pen?
25:
Don't touch me. I had to fend off
some beasts while I was out, and
am not in the mood to deal with
YOU.
34:
Marly, welcome back! We finished
making the potion you suggeste—
36:
Good. Grab what you need and get
ready to go. Soldiers could be here
any second!
40:
Here's the plan: sneak out of the
village, then head north and cross
the Snakespit River.
41:
There's a rebel fortress just on the
other side. I can't guarantee they'll
help you, but they're better than the
soldiers here, if nothing else.
45:
What about you, Marly? Will you be
all right?
58:
I can distract them while you
escape, and Marly won't be
punished.
63:
But then what will happen to YOU,
Stella?!
65:
You possess great powers essential
to our mission, while I contribute
nothing. Marly, take ME while Stella
runs!
74:
Please. Both of you run. Don't worry
about me.
78:
I know helping you won't bring my
girls back, but I'm not making the
same mistake twice.
80: I don't want any more regrets. Okay?
92:
We'll get through this! We WILL
escape!
101:
Well, well, well... Fancy seeing you
here.
109:
But I should be dead? See, I DID warn
you about the whole "daemons
can't die" thing.
118:
Alrighty boys, grab bootleg Stella
and... Uh. Do whatever with the other
human, I guess? Off ya go!
122:
All I ever do is wait for someone else
to save me.
125:
But you know what? I never wanted
to be a helpless little princess.
137: So I'm done. I'm done pretending!
145:
THE WITCH OF BURNING BLOOD'S
DAUGHTER!
155: A fine speech, King of Man.
163:
I will see to this pest. You must
continue your quest, Lilith Stratos!
170:
I'm trusting you to defend Stella and
the Mark.
173:
Adjudicus and the others should be
nearby. Hurry!
181:
Stella. I look forward to speaking
with you again. Until then, stay safe.
189:
Nuh-uh, you're gonna DIE, elf! Die,
DIE, DIEEE!
190:
If you won't join us, then we don't
need you!
200: That blast of wind... Look, it's Estariel!
204:
Yeah, saw it too! And the two specks
down over THERE have gotta be
Stella and Lilith!
208:
They're headed the wrong way!
They're going to hit a dead end!
213:
Let's go! We have to rejoin them
before—*gasp*
216:
Hah! Looks like we've got you now,
humans!
217:
You're gonna be fresh meat for our
daemons!
221: As if! We don't have time for you!
